cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.GR (Computer Graphics): The paper focuses on designing 3D objects and proposes an interactive sketch-to-design system, which is a common topic in computer graphics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses pre-learned part-based contextual information to allow the user to quickly explore different combinations of parts, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the scope of AI.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper mentions pre-segmented 3D models, which could involve computer vision techniques for segmentation.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper proposes an interactive system for designing 3D objects, which involves the interaction between humans and computers.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with 3D models and proposes a system for designing new variations from existing shapes, which could be considered as a multimedia application.
